data.name: Home_p1
data.value: The goal of drug logistics management information system is automatization of the process of the distribution, formation of demand and monitoring system for the drug and medical goods, that are centralized procured by the ministry of health or received humanitarian way. The system is designed for identified users. Each user of the system enters the appropriate login and password, then the user is automatically provided by the system has its own role and responsibilities of the respective interface.

data.name: Home_p2
data.value: Organization section established the opportunity to create and submit a product order, satisfying the demands of the track, manage the cost of medicines and medical goods, watch the movement of the storage facility, the picture of the remains of the maintenance period, as well as the return of product to other organization.

data.name: Home_p3
data.value: Storage section lets to create a warehouse and input the list of the medicine, medical goods, manage products through other warehouses. Section is intended to manage the requests submitted by the organizations, taking into account the reserve balance, the expire date of the products, the consumption of the product by facility in previous periods and other indicators. The debiting function of the warehouse based on the requests satisfied by the storage is carried out by means of the invoices, which enables to fix the date of the recording and date when the product will be ready for delivery, thereby completing the process of satisfying requests.

data.name: Home_p4
data.value: Reports section lets get standard reports, which were approved on 27.04.2012 N 926-A decree of the Minister of Health.

data.name: Home_p5
data.value: Management section allows to manage databases used in the system , manage the system users roles.

data.name: Home_p6
data.value: Messages section allows users to exchange messages in the system.

data.name: Home_p7
data.value: Help section provides a guide to using the system.

data.name: Login_Article
data.value: This system was designed under the grant AAG-111-G-10-002 signed between US Government and the RA Government "Health and social services to improve the efficiency of the fight against tuberculosis, maternal and child health, and family planning / reproductive health" for the purpose of the improving transparency and accountability in the system of provision of public services, including the purchase and distribution of medicine, medical goods and services.

data.value: Medicines and Medical Products Integrated Logistic Management Information System (MLMIS) (For the management of the distribution of the state centralized procured drugs, including for contraceptives)
